It can be seen that the variables such as 'src_bytes', 'dst_bytes', 'land', 'urgent', 'num_failed_logins', 'num_compromised', 'root_shell', 'su_attempted', 'num_root', 'num_file_creations', 'num_shells', 'num_outbound_cmds', 'is_host_login' have a very less correlation with the target label. Thus, we remove these columns/attributes.¶

Deep Learning Models¶

Convolutional Neural Network with 3 convolutional layers¶

In [116]:
cnn_model = keras.Sequential()
cnn_model.add(keras.layers.Conv1D(8, 3, padding="same", input_shape = (28, 1), activation = "relu"))
cnn_model.add(keras.layers.MaxPooling1D(pool_size=(2)))
cnn_model.add(keras.layers.Conv1D(16, 3, padding="same", activation="relu"))
cnn_model.add(keras.layers.MaxPooling1D(pool_size=(2)))
cnn_model.add(keras.layers.Conv1D(32, 3, padding="same", activation="relu"))
cnn_model.add(keras.layers.MaxPooling1D(pool_size=(2)))
cnn_model.add(keras.layers.Flatten())
cnn_model.add(keras.layers.Dense(32, activation="relu"))
cnn_model.add(keras.layers.Dense(23, activation="softmax"))
cnn_model.summary()
